Turn on coredump
/etc/systemd/coredump.conf
[Coredump]
Storage=external
Compress=yes
ProcessSizeMax=2G
ExternalSizeMax=10G

systemctl daemon-reload

[root@ods-db-01 ~]$ cat /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern
|/usr/lib/systemd/systemd-coredump %P %u %g %s %t %c %h %e

You can force a "fake" crash on a simple command (like sleep) to see if it saves:

Open a terminal and run: sleep 100 &
Kill it with a "QUIT" signal: kill -SIGQUIT $!
Check the list: coredumpctl list


coredumpctl list postgres
TIME                            PID   UID   GID SIG COREFILE  EXE
